</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/13670692-lita">Lita</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I would have been pleased if my children would have expressed an interest in Rumi at14. Rumi is sensuous sometimes, but not overtly sexual. At 14 I re<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I would have been pleased if my children would have expressed an interest in Rumi at14. Rumi is sensuous sometimes, but not overtly sexual. At 14 I read Walt Whitman's co!lection. I was a bit challenged by the homoerotic content of that Calamus poems, but I handled it fine. If a 14 year old is seriously into poetry, I suspect that they are prepared for Rumi.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
