<div id="review_22952959" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/22952959" />
    <a title="Feral" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1185929-feral"><img alt="Feral" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1211749802p2/1185929.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/22952959?book_show_action=true">May 25, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Feral" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Feral" href="/user/show/1185929-feral">Feral</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Softcover 0965064871" href="/book/show/3102925-the-essential-rumi">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer22952959" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7722477555290844096">Again, a translator brought the text alive for me. Barks is, himself, a poet and his translations are more like interpretations. I think it is the only way to go with translating poetry. The translator must essentially make a new poem in the new language for it to work. I became a Rumi-aholic, but rarely stray from Barks translations.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

